# {{APP_DISPLAY_NAME}} — Governance & Technical Standards

> This document defines the coding standards, architecture decisions, and promotion rules
> for this Power Apps Code App. All contributors must follow these guidelines.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version | Notes |
|-------|-----------|---------|-------|
| Framework | React | 18.x | Functional components only, no class components |
| Language | TypeScript | Strict mode | `strict: true` in tsconfig.json |
| Build | Vite | 6.x | Dev server on port 3000 |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | 4.x | Utility-first, no custom CSS unless necessary |
| State | Zustand | Latest | Single store per domain, no prop drilling |
| Data | Power Apps SDK | `@microsoft/power-apps` | Generated services from pac CLI |
| Deployment | pac CLI | Latest | `pac code push` for all environments |

## Architecture Rules

### File Organization
- `src/config.ts` — ONLY file that reads `import.meta.env`. Everything else imports from here.
- `src/services/` — Backend abstraction layer. Always includes localStorage fallback.
- `src/store/` — Zustand stores. One store per bounded context.
- `src/components/` — Reusable UI components.
- `src/pages/` — Top-level page components (one per route/view).
- `src/generated/` — pac CLI generated files. **NEVER hand-edit.**

### Backend Pattern
- Every data operation uses the timeout+fallback pattern (see dataService.ts).
- NEVER check `window.powerAppsBridge` — it is always undefined.
- The app must work at localhost with localStorage. No exceptions.

### Environment Configuration
- `.env` is gitignored. Each developer and environment has their own copy.
- `.env.example` is committed with placeholder values.
- `power.config.json` is gitignored. Contains environment-specific Power Platform IDs.
- Vite substitutes env vars at BUILD time. Always rebuild after changing `.env`.

## Code Quality

### TypeScript
- `strict: true` — no `any` types unless absolutely necessary (document why in a comment).
- All component props have explicit interfaces.
- All service functions have explicit return types.

### Tailwind CSS
- Use utility classes directly in JSX. No separate CSS files unless for complex animations.
- Consistent spacing scale — stick to Tailwind's defaults.
- Dark mode support via `dark:` variants where applicable.

### Components
- Functional components only. No class components.
- Custom hooks for shared logic (prefix with `use`).
- Error boundaries around data-fetching components.
- Loading and empty states for every list/table view.

## PR Checklist

Before merging any pull request, verify:

- [ ] TypeScript compiles with zero errors (`npx tsc --noEmit`)
- [ ] Build succeeds (`npm run build`)
- [ ] App loads at localhost:3000 with localStorage backend
- [ ] No `import.meta.env` usage outside `config.ts`
- [ ] No hand-edits to files in `src/generated/` or `.power/`
- [ ] `.env.example` updated if new env vars were added
- [ ] DEPLOYMENT.md updated if deployment steps changed

## Environment Promotion Rules

| From | To | Requires |
|------|----|----------|
| DEV | TEST | PR review + build passes + dev smoke-test |
| TEST | UAT | QA sign-off + stakeholder demo |
| UAT | PROD | Business owner approval + change request |

### Promotion Steps
1. Update `.env` with target environment values
2. Update `power.config.json` with target environment ID
3. Verify backend resources (SP list / DV table) exist in target
4. `pac auth create --environment <TARGET_ENV_ID>`
5. `pac code add-data-source` with target connection ID
6. `npm run build && pac code push`
7. Smoke-test in Power Apps player

